item - DublinCore - Title - Display: Korean Independence Movement. Page 12
item - DublinCore - Description: This man is more fortunate.  He has a bayonet stab in his eye.  He was taken into one of the mission (Christian) hospitals, where he received treatment.  The picture was taken one week after the man received the wound.

item - MODS - RepositoryName: Burke Library at Union Theological Seminary, Columbia University
item - DublinCore - Title - Display: Korean Independence Movement. Page 11
item - DublinCore - Description: To show their sympathy with the independence demonstrators and as a pacific means to demand the release of those who have been arrested, all Korean shopkeepers have closed their shops.  Japanese soldiers are seen patrolling the streets with fixed bayonets.

item - MODS - RepositoryName: Burke Library at Union Theological Seminary, Columbia University
item - DublinCore - Title - Display: Korean Independence Movement. Page 10
item - DublinCore - Description: Another piece of Japanese brutality.  The leg of a Korean is beaten flat after being shot at.

item - MODS - RepositoryName: Burke Library at Union Theological Seminary, Columbia University
item - DublinCore - Title - Display: Korean Independence Movement. Page 9
item - DublinCore - Description: After the first surprise the Japanese authorities turned loose the soldiers on the Koreans.  This picture shows how one of them was slashed and cut up all over the body by merciless Japanese soldiers.

item - MODS - RepositoryName: Burke Library at Union Theological Seminary, Columbia University
item - DublinCore - Title - Display: Korean Independence Movement. Page 8
item - DublinCore - Description: Japanese soldiers dot the streets of Seoul and other important cities in Korea like flies--one Japanese soldier at intervals of five houses.  A busy market square presents a deserted air.

item - MODS - RepositoryName: Burke Library at Union Theological Seminary, Columbia University
item - DublinCore - Title - Display: Korean Independence Movement. Page 7

item - MODS - RepositoryName: Burke Library at Union Theological Seminary, Columbia University

item - MODS - RepositoryName: Burke Library at Union Theological Seminary, Columbia University
item - DublinCore - Title - Display: Korean Independence Movement. Page 5
item - DublinCore - Description: Demonstration for independence in the Park. The Koreans are seen shouting "Mansei" with their hands up in the air.  Not a single man is armed.

item - DublinCore - Title - Display: Korean Independence Movement. Page 4
